</p>

<#t>
  《施氏食獅史》 |
  "{An} History of Mr~<^e>Shih</^e>'s Eating of Lions"
</#t>
<ul>
  <li>施氏：
    Mr~<^e>Shih</^e>;
    \lit {he with} surname <^e>Shih</^e>
  </li>
  <li>史：
    history;
    \or record
  </li>
</ul>

<#t>
  石室詩士施氏，嗜獅，誓食十獅。 |
  {The} poet Mr~<^e>Shih</^e> of {a} stone house:
  {he} liked lions,
  {and} sware to eat ten lions.
</#t>
<ul>
  <li>石：
    stone;
    \or rock
  </li>
  <li>室：
    house;
    \or room
  </li>
  <li>詩士：
    poet;
    \lit poem scholar
  </li>
  <li>嗜：
    liked;
    \or {was} fond of
  </li>
  <li>誓：
    <@>
      sware
      | https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/sware#English
      | (Verb) simple past tense of swear
    </@> to;
    \or took oath to
  </li>
</ul>

<#t>
  氏時時適市視獅。 |
  Mr~{<^e>Shih</^e>} went to {the} market all the time {to} view lions.
</#t>
<ul>
  <li>氏<br>
    Here, 施 has been
    dropped from 施氏.
  </li>
  <li>時時：
    all the time;
    \or often
  </li>
  <li>適：往也；
    went to
  </li>
</ul>

<#t>
  十時，適十獅適市。是時，適施氏適市。 |
  {At} ten o'clock, ten lions {had} just arrived at {the} market.
  {At} this time, Mr~<^e>Shih</^e> {had also} just arrived at {the} market.
</#t>
<ul>
  <li>十時：
    ten o'clock<br>
    This is a modern term; perhaps "tenth hour" would be a better rendering.
    Classically, 時 means 時辰, which are
    <@>
      named two-hour intervals
      | https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Earthly_Branches
      | Wikipedia: Earthly Branches
    </@>
    rather than numbered one-hour intervals.
  </li>
  <li>適：
    {had} just;
    \or {happened to have} just
  </li>
  <li>適：至也；
    arrived at
  </li>
</ul>

<#t>
  氏視是十獅，恃矢勢，使是十獅逝世。 |
  Mr~{<^e>Shih</^e>} saw these ten lions,
  {and}, relying on {the} situational {advantage} of the arrow,
  made these ten lions pass away.
</#t>
<ul>
  <li>勢：
    situational {advantage};
    \or influence
  </li>
  <li>使：
    made;
    \or caused
  </li>
</ul>

<#t>
  氏拾是十獅屍，適石室。 |
  Mr~{<^e>Shih</^e>} picked up {the} carcasses of these ten lions,
  {and} went to {the} stone house.
</#t>

<#t>
  石室濕，氏使侍拭石室。 |
  {The} stone house wet,
  Mr~{<^e>Shih</^e>} made {his} servants wipe {the} stone house.
</#t>

<#t>
  石室拭，氏始試食是十獅屍。 |
  {The} stone house wiped,
  Mr~{<^e>Shih</^e>} began to try eating {the} carcasses of these ten lions.
</#t>
<ul>
  <li>始：
    began to;
    \or started to
  </li>
  <li>試食：
    try eating;
    \or try for taste;
    \or taste test
  </li>
</ul>

<#t>
  食時，始識是十獅屍，實十石獅屍。 |
  {Only} when eating,
  {did he} first know {that the} carcasses of these ten lions,
  {were} actually {the} carcasses of ten stone lions.
</#t>
<ul>
  <li>始：
    first;
    \or begin to
  </li>
  <li>實：
    actually;
    \or in fact;
    \or really
  </li>
</ul>

<#t>
  試釋是事。 |
  Try to interpret these events.
</#t>
<ul>
  <li>試：
    try to;
    \or attempt to
  </li>
  <li>是事：
    these events;
    \or this incident
  </li>
</ul>

